Put in enough for every member of your household plus an additional 3 for anyone who happens to be visiting when the nuclear attack warning is issued or anyone who is immediately nearby when the warning is issued. Make up the beds with sheets and duvets rather than blankets - blankets are more likely to be eaten by moths and other such creatures. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/05/Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/05/Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Put a space blanket (foil blanket that folds up compactly) on each bed - that way if any sheets or blankets to get eaten or rot, or if there is an extreme in temperatures that means that a few sheets and a duvet would not be enough to keep each person warm. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cd/Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cd/Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Bunker-in-Preperation-for-a-Nuclear-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
